31/01/2003
KOZLODUY, Bulgaria -- Removal of residual nuclear fuel from the second reactor of Bulgaria's nuclear power plant started on Thursday (30 January), under the supervision of the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA). 
Decommissioning of the first and second nuclear reactors commenced in December 2002 and they were finally shut down by 31 December. 
The purpose of IAEA mission is to assure that Bulgaria is implementing its obligations under the Non-Proliferation of Nuclear Weapons Treaty that Bulgaria signed in 1970. 
(BTA - 30/01/03)
